{{ja-kanjitab|から|yomi=k}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=から|-}}.

Originally referred to the {{w|Gaya confederacy}}, an independent state in the south of the Korean peninsula in the years 42-562 CE.  Over time, the meaning extended to refer in general to the Korean peninsula and China, expanding further just before and during the {{w|Edo period}} to refer to foreign lands in general.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DJS">{{R:Daijisen}}</ref>

* {{sense|usually China in the {{w|Tang dynasty}}, and foreign lands in general}} {{ja-l|唐}}
* {{sense|usually Korea}} {{ja-l|韓}}
* {{sense|specifically the Gaya confederacy}} {{ja-l|加羅}}, {{ja-l|伽羅}}, {{ja-l|迦羅}}

